# Brand Migration Rule — Rename and Reposition

This codebase must be migrated away from the original branding and repositioned as a new product.

## Required tasks during migration
- identify all occurrences of the old product name
- identify logo/icon/metadata references
- identify package names, titles, descriptions, docs strings, telemetry labels, URLs, and environment variables tied to the old brand
- replace them safely and consistently

## Scope of branding review
Check at minimum:
- package.json files
- app window titles
- frontend labels
- docs/readmes
- favicon/logo/icon assets
- environment variables
- metadata/config files
- internal constants
- comments only if they leak product identity externally

## Migration constraints
- do not blindly replace strings without understanding context
- do not break imports/package references during rename
- prefer staged renaming where necessary
- preserve technical behavior while changing branding

## Output expectation
For each branding task, provide:
- files affected
- rename strategy
- risk of breakage
- safe implementation order
